<TITLE> Muslim countries should mobilise resources: Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)- Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina today called for muslim countries to pool their resources, technologies and market opportunities. The PM was speaking at the Sixth World Islamic Economic Forum (WIFE), at the Plenary Hall of Kuala Lumpur Convention Centre, Wednesday, reports state owned news agency Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha. Urging representatives from the participating countries to find new solutions that "conform to our own economic policies," Sheikh Hasina said that there was a need to "shield ourselves from the uncertainties of the external financial system to protect ourselves from unexpected economic upheavals in the future." Terming WIFE as a timely initiative to mobilize the resources of Muslim majority countries in order to create a synergy for their own development, Hasina said the forum would also act as a bridge for synchronizing financial systems and economic activities of Muslim nations with the rest of the world. The prime minister also called upon the international companies attending the conference to come forward with extensive investments in various sectors in Bangladesh to help realize the 'Vision 2021' of her government. A total of 2000 participants, including heads of states and governments, and business leaders from 67 Muslims countries across the globe, are participating in the conference. bd
